  "content": "# schema design\n\nPatterns and conventions for designing document model state schemas in the Powerhouse ecosystem.\n\n## Type Naming\n- [[state type names use XState not XGlobalState]] \u2014 the code generator expects `<Name>State`, not `<Name>GlobalState`\n\n## Arrays and Objects\n- [[arrays in state schemas must use mandatory notation]] \u2014 `[ObjectType!]!` with `OID!` fields for array items\n\n## Required vs Optional Fields\n- [[most state schema fields should be optional to support empty documents]] \u2014 documents start empty; use `!` sparingly\n\n## Input Design\n- [[input types should reflect user intent with simple specific fields]] \u2014 flat, descriptive inputs over nested structures\n- [[operation design uses descriptive names and includes examples and errors]] \u2014 naming and documentation standards\n\n## Scope\n- [[global scope shares state among all users while local scope is private]] \u2014 when to use each scope\n\n## Operation Design\n- [[one operation per user intent keeps concerns separated]] \u2014 one user action = one operation\n\n## Document Model Structure\n- [[document model structure has metadata specifications and modules]] \u2014 the three layers of a model\n- [[document models have 37 available operations across 7 categories]] \u2014 full operation taxonomy\n\n---\n\nTopics:\n- [[index]]",
